				\begin{document}$${\bf{e}}_{\theta _i}$$\end{document}eθi in the first equation and ωi in the second equation. The sudden change from the behaviour of the inactive particles to that of normal particles collapsed the network structure. Once the ratio of inactive particles returned to its initial value, the network reformed. Although light stimulation leads to both reversal and forward acceleration of worms, at least we can conclude that the decrease of halted worms is one of the main causes of the instability of the bundles.

